  { name: 'NF Extra C Tablets 30s', url: 'https://dwatson.pk/nf-extra-c-30s-tablets.html', price: 690, display: 'Rs. 690' },
  { name: 'High C 1000 Sachet', url: 'https://dwatson.pk/high-c-1000-sachet.html', price: 250, display: 'Rs. 250', badge: 'Best Budget Trial' },
];

const faqs = [
  { q: 'How much vitamin C should I take daily?', a: 'The recommended daily allowance is 75mg for women and 90mg for men, with an upper safe limit of 2,000mg per day for adults. Supplemental doses of 500–1,000mg are common and generally well tolerated; doses above 1,000mg offer diminishing absorption.' },
  { q: 'What is the best vitamin C supplement in Pakistan?', a: 'For a straightforward daily 1,000mg dose, NF Nutri C 1000mg (about Rs. 990 for 30 tablets at D.Watson) offers the best combination of dose, brand reliability, and price. If you want added immune support, NF Nutra C Plus combines 500mg vitamin C with zinc for about Rs. 690.' },
  { q: 'Vitamin C tablets or sachets — which is better?', a: 'Both deliver the same ascorbic acid. Sachets like Core C dissolve into a drink, which suits people who dislike swallowing tablets, and the sugar-free version is a better fit for diabetic users. Tablets are cheaper per dose in bulk packs like NF Extra C 90s.' },
  { q: 'Does vitamin C actually prevent colds?', a: 'Evidence shows regular vitamin C supplementation modestly shortens cold duration (by roughly 8% in adults) and may reduce severity, but it does not reliably prevent colds in the general population. Its clearest benefits are for people with low dietary intake or high physical stress.' },
  { q: 'Can I take vitamin C with zinc?', a: 'Yes — the combination is common and well tolerated, and both nutrients play roles in normal immune function. Combined products like NF Nutra C Plus C500 + Zinc simplify this into one tablet. Take with food if you experience mild stomach upset.' },
];
