  <h2>How to choose a vitamin C supplement</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Dose:</strong> 500mg daily is plenty for maintenance; 1,000mg is the common
    choice during illness or high stress — stay under the 2,000mg daily upper limit.
    <strong>Format:</strong> tablets are cheapest per dose; sugar-free sachets suit diabetic
    users and tablet-averse family members. <strong>Combos:</strong> add zinc during flu
    season. Take vitamin C with food if you have a sensitive stomach, and see the full range
    at <a href="https://dwatson.pk/health-supplements/vitamins-a-z/vitamin-c.html">dwatson.pk's
    Vitamin C category</a>.
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>
